Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz} if necessary; chop into bite-size pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Place kale in a #large bowl{}; add a drizzle of @olive oil{} (large drizzle for 4 servings) and a pinch of @salt{}. Using your hands, massage until leaves are tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} (large drizzle for 4 servings) in a #small pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in lemon zest, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @nutritional yeast{2%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @vegan mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, remaining garlic powder, remaining nutritional yeast, @Worcestershire sauce{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and juice from one lemon wedge (1 tsp Worcestershire sauce and juice from two lemon wedges for 4 servings). (Save any remaining Worcestershire sauce for another use.) Set aside.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} and toast until golden brown.

Lightly drizzle cut sides with @olive oil{}. Halve on a diagonal.

To bowl with kale, add broccoli, beans, and dressing; toss to combine. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide salad between plates. Top with toasted panko and as many @Korean chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Serve with ciabatta points and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.